title: Samsung’s Wireless Frame Pro TV Is a Disaster (And I’m Stuck With It)
description: Samsung's new $2,200 Wireless Frame Pro TV is AWFUL! Watch it implode under latency, bugs, and edge‑lit lies. Save on the Rhinoshield AirX at checkout using code "SNAZZYLABS" - https://url.rhinoshield.io/SNAZZYLABS Follow Snazzy Labs on Twitter - https://twitter.com/snazzylabs   Follow me on Bluesky - https://snazzy.fm/UW Follow me on Threads - https://snazzy.fm/XV Follow me on Mastodon - https://snazzy.fm/NN Follow me on Instagram - https://instagram.com/snazzyq  In this Samsung Frame Pro review, I explain why the $2,200 “wireless” TV is a disaster: the Wireless One Connect box causes latency, stutters, and constant disconnects, the micro‑HDMI 2.1 port lacks eARC/ARC for soundbars, Wi‑Fi 7/6GHz interference breaks stability, and HDMI‑CEC mangles Art Mode power behavior. Despite the matte panel and convincing Art Mode, the edge‑lit “Neo QLED powered by mini‑LED” display delivers poor contrast, vertical banding, smeary night scenes, and unhinged default picture settings—with no Dolby Vision. Software is painfully slow (TV Plus bloat), setup is infuriating (mounting/stud issues, cable routing), and even Samsung’s S801D soundbar drops audio over Wi‑Fi, forcing a lower‑quality Bluetooth fallback. If you want a main TV, buy an OLED; for an art TV, cheaper Hisense/TCL models are better. description: #8k @Review #television #samsung #miniled #neoqled8k   The Samsung QN990F is an 8K TV series. It features a wireless One Connect Box (WOCB) capable of transmitting 8K signals at 120Hz over a distance of up to 10 meters.   Thanks to its Omni-Directional technology powered by WiFi 7, the signal can pass through obstacles in the room, offering flexible placement. The WOCB is also significantly more compact (62% smaller) than its wired predecessor.  This series includes both 85-inch and 98-inch models. Under the hood, it packs serious intelligence with Microsoft Copilot AI integrated directly into the Tizen OS.  The processor is powered by 762 neural networks, and for gamers, it supports VRR up to 240Hz for silky-smooth motion.

title: How To Download Playstore on LG Smart TV
description: Want to know how to download Play Store on LG Smart TV? In this video, I’ll show you the real working methods to use Google Play Store apps on your LG Smart TV and clear all confusion.  👉 Option 1 (Best Method): Connect an external device such as Google TV Stick, Fire Stick, Mi Box, or any Android TV Box via HDMI. This way, you’ll get full access to the Google Play Store and all Android apps.  👉 Option 2: Use the built-in browser on LG TV to open the Play Store. However, keep in mind that you cannot directly install apps this way.  💡 Why Play Store is missing on LG Smart TV? LG Smart TVs run on webOS, not Android. That’s why Play Store cannot be directly installed.
